[0.011, "o", "\u001b[?2026h\u001b[38;2;215;119;87m ‚ñê\u001b[48;2;0;0;0m‚ñõ‚ñà‚ñà‚ñà‚ñú\u001b[49m‚ñå\u001b[3C\u001b[39m\u001b[1mClaude\u001b[1CCode\u001b[1C\u001b[22m\u001b[38;2;153;153;153mv2.1.84\u001b[39m\r\r\n\u001b[38;2;215;119;87m‚ñù‚ñú\u001b[48;2;0;0;0m‚ñà‚ñà‚ñà‚ñà‚ñà\u001b[49m‚ñõ‚ñò\u001b[2C\u001b[38;2;153;153;153mOpus\u001b[1C4.6\u001b[1C(1M\u001b[1Ccontext)\u001b[1C¬∑\u001b[1CClaude\u001b[1CMax\u001b[39m\r\r\n\u001b[38;2;215;119;87m \u001b[1C‚ñò‚ñò\u001b[1C‚ñù‚ñù\u001b[4C\u001b[38;2;153;153;153m~/projects/talks/oreilly-codecon-march-2026/demo-2\u001b[39m\r\r\n\r\r\n\u001b[38;2;136;136;136m‚îÄ‚îÄ‚îÄ‚îÄ‚îÄ‚îÄ‚îÄ‚îÄ‚îÄ‚îÄ‚îÄ‚îÄ‚îÄ‚îÄ‚îÄ‚îÄ‚îÄ‚îÄ‚îÄ‚îÄ‚îÄ‚îÄ‚îÄ‚îÄ‚îÄ‚îÄ‚îÄ‚îÄ‚îÄ‚îÄ‚îÄ‚îÄ‚îÄ‚îÄ‚îÄ‚îÄ‚îÄ‚îÄ‚îÄ‚îÄ‚îÄ‚îÄ‚îÄ‚îÄ‚îÄ‚îÄ‚îÄ‚îÄ‚îÄ‚îÄ‚îÄ‚îÄ‚îÄ‚îÄ‚îÄ‚îÄ‚îÄ‚îÄ‚îÄ‚îÄ‚îÄ‚îÄ‚îÄ‚îÄ‚îÄ‚îÄ‚îÄ‚îÄ‚îÄ‚îÄ‚îÄ‚îÄ‚îÄ‚îÄ‚îÄ‚îÄ‚îÄ‚îÄ‚îÄ‚îÄ‚îÄ‚îÄ‚îÄ‚îÄ‚îÄ‚îÄ‚îÄ‚îÄ‚îÄ‚îÄ‚îÄ‚îÄ‚îÄ‚îÄ‚îÄ‚îÄ‚îÄ‚îÄ‚îÄ‚îÄ‚îÄ‚îÄ‚îÄ‚îÄ‚îÄ‚îÄ‚îÄ‚îÄ‚îÄ‚îÄ‚îÄ‚îÄ‚îÄ‚îÄ‚îÄ‚îÄ‚îÄ‚îÄ‚îÄ‚îÄ‚îÄ‚îÄ‚îÄ‚îÄ‚îÄ‚îÄ‚îÄ‚îÄ‚îÄ‚îÄ‚îÄ‚îÄ‚îÄ‚îÄ‚îÄ‚îÄ‚îÄ‚îÄ‚îÄ‚îÄ‚îÄ‚îÄ‚îÄ‚îÄ‚îÄ‚îÄ‚îÄ\u001b[39m\r\r\n‚ùØ¬Ý\u001b[7m \u001b[27m\r\r\n\u001b[38;2;136;136;136m‚îÄ‚îÄ‚îÄ‚îÄ‚îÄ‚îÄ‚îÄ‚îÄ‚îÄ‚îÄ‚îÄ‚îÄ‚îÄ‚îÄ‚îÄ‚îÄ‚îÄ‚îÄ‚îÄ‚îÄ‚îÄ‚îÄ‚îÄ‚îÄ‚îÄ‚îÄ‚îÄ‚îÄ‚îÄ‚îÄ‚îÄ‚îÄ‚îÄ‚îÄ‚îÄ‚îÄ‚îÄ"]
[0.000, "o", "‚îÄ‚îÄ‚îÄ‚îÄ‚îÄ‚îÄ‚îÄ‚îÄ‚îÄ‚îÄ‚îÄ‚îÄ‚îÄ‚îÄ‚îÄ‚îÄ‚îÄ‚îÄ‚îÄ‚îÄ‚îÄ‚îÄ‚îÄ‚îÄ‚îÄ‚îÄ‚îÄ‚îÄ‚îÄ‚îÄ‚îÄ‚îÄ‚îÄ‚îÄ‚îÄ‚îÄ‚îÄ‚îÄ‚îÄ‚îÄ‚îÄ‚îÄ‚îÄ‚îÄ‚îÄ‚îÄ‚îÄ‚îÄ‚îÄ‚îÄ‚îÄ‚îÄ‚îÄ‚îÄ‚îÄ‚îÄ‚îÄ‚îÄ‚îÄ‚îÄ‚îÄ‚îÄ‚îÄ‚îÄ‚îÄ‚îÄ‚îÄ‚îÄ‚îÄ‚îÄ‚îÄ‚îÄ‚îÄ‚îÄ‚îÄ‚îÄ‚îÄ‚îÄ‚îÄ‚îÄ‚îÄ‚îÄ‚îÄ‚îÄ‚îÄ‚îÄ‚îÄ‚îÄ‚îÄ‚îÄ‚îÄ‚îÄ‚îÄ‚îÄ‚îÄ‚îÄ‚îÄ‚îÄ‚îÄ‚îÄ‚îÄ‚îÄ‚îÄ‚îÄ‚îÄ‚îÄ‚îÄ‚îÄ‚îÄ‚îÄ\u001b[39m\r\r\n\u001b[2C\u001b[38;2;255;107;128m‚èµ‚èµ\u001b[1Cbypass\u001b[1Cpermissions\u001b[1Con\u001b[38;2;153;153;153m (shift+tab\u001b[1Cto\u001b[1Ccycle)\u001b[80C‚óê\u001b[1Cmedium\u001b[1C¬∑\u001b[1C/effort\u001b[39m\r\r\n\u001b[2C\u001b[3A\u001b[?2026l"]
[0.036, "o", "\u001b]0;‚ÝÇ Claude Code\u0007"]
[0.007, "o", "\u001b[?2026h\u001b[2D\u001b[3B\r\u001b[4A\u001b[48;2;55;55;55m\u001b[38;2;80;80;80m‚ùØ \u001b[38;2;255;255;255mYou have a working bookmarks manager app called \"Link Shelf\" with Express and SQLite. The existing code has:\u001b[39m                                     \r\u001b[1B\u001b[38;2;255;255;255m- db.js: SQLite data layer with CRUD operations\u001b[39m                                                                                                    \r\u001b[1B\u001b[38;2;255;255;255m- validation.js: input validation and sanitization\u001b[39m                                                                                                 \r\u001b[1B\u001b[38;2;255;255;255m- server.js: Express API with endpoints for /api/links (GET, POST, PUT, DELETE)\u001b[39m                                                                    \u001b[49m\r\r\n\u001b[48;2;55;55;55m\u001b[38;2;255;255;255m- test.js: test suite\u001b[39m                                                                                                                              \u001b[49m\r\r\n\u001b[48;2;55;55;55m                                                   "]
[0.000, "o", "                                                                                                \u001b[49m\r\r\n\u001b[48;2;55;55;55m\u001b[38;2;255;255;255mAdd SEARCH functionality to this app using Agent Teams. Create a team with 3 teammates:\u001b[39m                                                            \u001b[49m\r\r\n\u001b[48;2;55;55;55m                                                                                                                                                   \u001b[49m\r\r\n\u001b[48;2;55;55;55m\u001b[38;2;255;255;255m1. BACKEND TEAMMATE: Add a search endpoint GET /api/links/search?q=<query> that searches links by title, url, and description using SQL LIKE \u001b[39m      \u001b[49m\r\r\n\u001b[48;2;55;55;55m\u001b[38;2;255;255;255mqueries. Add a searchLinks(query) function to db.js and wire up the route in server.js.\u001b[39m                                                            \u001b[49m\r\r\n\u001b[48;2;55;55;55m                                                                                                                                                   \u001b"]
[0.000, "o", "[49m\r\r\n\u001b[48;2;55;55;55m\u001b[38;2;255;255;255m2. FRONTEND TEAMMATE: Add a simple search HTML page at GET /search that has a search input with debounced requests to the search API, and displays\u001b[39m \u001b[49m\r\r\n\u001b[48;2;55;55;55m\u001b[38;2;255;255;255m results as a list of clickable links. Serve it from server.js.\u001b[39m                                                                                    \u001b[49m\r\r\n\u001b[48;2;55;55;55m                                                                                                                                                   \u001b[49m\r\r\n\u001b[48;2;55;55;55m\u001b[38;2;255;255;255m3. TEST TEAMMATE: Add search-specific tests to test.js that verify: search returns matching results, search with no matches returns empty array, \u001b[39m  \u001b[49m\r\r\n\u001b[48;2;55;55;55m\u001b[38;2;255;255;255msearch is case-insensitive, and the search endpoint validates input. This task DEPENDS on the backend teammate finishing the search API first.\u001b[39m     \u001b[49m\r\r\n\u001b[48;2;55;55;55m                                                  "]
[0.000, "o", "                                                                                                 \u001b[49m\r\r\n\u001b[48;2;55;55;55m\u001b[38;2;255;255;255mThe backend and frontend teammates should work IN PARALLEL. The test teammate should be BLOCKED until the backend API is done, then auto-unblock. \u001b[39m \u001b[49m\r\r\n\u001b[48;2;55;55;55m\u001b[38;2;255;255;255mThe backend teammate should send the frontend teammate a peer message with the API contract once the endpoint is built. Use the shared task list \u001b[39m  \u001b[49m\r\r\n\u001b[48;2;55;55;55m\u001b[38;2;255;255;255mwith dependency tracking.\u001b[39m                                                                                                                          \u001b[49m\r\r\n\u001b[48;2;55;55;55m                                                                                                                                                   \u001b[49m\r\r\n\r\r\n\u001b[38;2;215;119;87m¬∑\u001b[1CChannelling‚Ä¶\u001b[39m\r\r\n\r\r\n\u001b[38;2;136;136;136m‚îÄ‚îÄ‚îÄ‚îÄ‚îÄ‚îÄ‚îÄ‚îÄ‚îÄ‚îÄ‚îÄ‚îÄ‚îÄ‚îÄ‚îÄ‚îÄ‚îÄ‚îÄ‚îÄ‚îÄ‚îÄ‚îÄ‚îÄ‚îÄ‚îÄ‚îÄ‚îÄ‚îÄ‚îÄ‚îÄ"]
[0.000, "o", "‚îÄ‚îÄ‚îÄ‚îÄ‚îÄ‚îÄ‚îÄ‚îÄ‚îÄ‚îÄ‚îÄ‚îÄ‚îÄ‚îÄ‚îÄ‚îÄ‚îÄ‚îÄ‚îÄ‚îÄ‚îÄ‚îÄ‚îÄ‚îÄ‚îÄ‚îÄ‚îÄ‚îÄ‚îÄ‚îÄ‚îÄ‚îÄ‚îÄ‚îÄ‚îÄ‚îÄ‚îÄ‚îÄ‚îÄ‚îÄ‚îÄ‚îÄ‚îÄ‚îÄ‚îÄ‚îÄ‚îÄ‚îÄ‚îÄ‚îÄ‚îÄ‚îÄ‚îÄ‚îÄ‚îÄ‚îÄ‚îÄ‚îÄ‚îÄ‚îÄ‚îÄ‚îÄ‚îÄ‚îÄ‚îÄ‚îÄ‚îÄ‚îÄ‚îÄ‚îÄ‚îÄ‚îÄ‚îÄ‚îÄ‚îÄ‚îÄ‚îÄ‚îÄ‚îÄ‚îÄ‚îÄ‚îÄ‚îÄ‚îÄ‚îÄ‚îÄ‚îÄ‚îÄ‚îÄ‚îÄ‚îÄ‚îÄ‚îÄ‚îÄ‚îÄ‚îÄ‚îÄ‚îÄ‚îÄ‚îÄ‚îÄ‚îÄ‚îÄ‚îÄ‚îÄ‚îÄ‚îÄ‚îÄ‚îÄ‚îÄ‚îÄ‚îÄ‚îÄ‚îÄ‚îÄ‚îÄ‚îÄ\u001b[39m\r\r\n\u001b[38;2;153;153;153m‚ùØ¬Ý\u001b[39m\u001b[7m \u001b[27m\r\r\n\u001b[38;2;136;136;136m‚îÄ‚îÄ‚îÄ‚îÄ‚îÄ‚îÄ‚îÄ‚îÄ‚îÄ‚îÄ‚îÄ‚îÄ‚îÄ‚îÄ‚îÄ‚îÄ‚îÄ‚îÄ‚îÄ‚îÄ‚îÄ‚îÄ‚îÄ‚îÄ‚îÄ‚îÄ‚îÄ‚îÄ‚îÄ‚îÄ‚îÄ‚îÄ‚îÄ‚îÄ‚îÄ‚îÄ‚îÄ‚îÄ‚îÄ‚îÄ‚îÄ‚îÄ‚îÄ‚îÄ‚îÄ‚îÄ‚îÄ‚îÄ‚îÄ‚îÄ‚îÄ‚îÄ‚îÄ‚îÄ‚îÄ‚îÄ‚îÄ‚îÄ‚îÄ‚îÄ‚îÄ‚îÄ‚îÄ‚îÄ‚îÄ‚îÄ‚îÄ‚îÄ‚îÄ‚îÄ‚îÄ‚îÄ‚îÄ‚îÄ‚îÄ‚îÄ‚îÄ‚îÄ‚îÄ‚îÄ‚îÄ‚îÄ‚îÄ‚îÄ‚îÄ‚îÄ‚îÄ‚îÄ‚îÄ‚îÄ‚îÄ‚îÄ‚îÄ‚îÄ‚îÄ‚îÄ‚îÄ‚îÄ‚îÄ‚îÄ‚îÄ‚îÄ‚îÄ‚îÄ‚îÄ‚îÄ‚îÄ‚îÄ‚îÄ‚îÄ‚îÄ‚îÄ‚îÄ‚îÄ‚îÄ‚îÄ‚îÄ‚îÄ‚îÄ‚îÄ‚îÄ‚îÄ‚îÄ‚îÄ‚îÄ‚îÄ‚îÄ‚îÄ‚îÄ‚îÄ‚îÄ‚îÄ‚îÄ‚îÄ‚îÄ‚îÄ‚îÄ‚îÄ‚îÄ‚îÄ‚îÄ‚îÄ‚îÄ‚îÄ‚îÄ‚îÄ‚îÄ\u001b[39m\r\r\n\u001b[2C\u001b[38;2;255;107;128m‚èµ‚èµ\u001b[1Cbypass\u001b[1Cpermissions\u001b[1Con\u001b[38;2;153;153;153m (shift+tab\u001b[1Cto\u001b[1Ccycle)\u001b[1C¬∑\u001b[1Cesc\u001b[1Cto\u001b[1Cinterrupt\u001b[61C‚óê\u001b[1Cmedium\u001b"]
